  "texts": [
    "Since LMs in general do have problems in confessing that they do not know about certain things, it is not surprising, that they invent similarities between the celebrities, e.g.",
    "common birthplace, age of dying, art or sport area and so on.Prompt engineeringshould only be an intermediate step towards better language models, since it should not be the task of a human to ask the question in a way that allows the LLM to give the correct answer, but the LLM should be trained in a way that allows it to understand all kinds of questions and always gives the best possible answer (given its training data).",
    "For Luminous for example, it made a great difference whether it is prompted with the context and question only, or there was a prefix \"question: \" before the actual question.",
    "It did not help to put the \"question: \" prefix before the context.",
    "With the prefix, the answers were much better than without."
  ],
